place_name: Mahesh Lunch Home - Seafood Specialty Restaurant (Juhu)
review_text: This place is located near JW Marriott, Juhu beach road. I have been to this place twice by now and trust me they serve really great sea food. Must must must recommend dish is their crab in Andhra style. Im not sure if you get it out of crab festival. I tried this first in their crab & wine festival and the taste just blown my mind so next time when I went there with my family after the fest, I requested to check if they can make that dish as its not in their regular menu. We also tried their Surmai in Maratha style, butter garlic prawns, bombil rava fry, mix fish soup. Every dish has its own different taste and everything we tried tastes great. We also tried few mock-tails (I dont remember the names now) but they were good too. The ambience is good, the service is top notch. Highly recommend place for seafood lover. The pricing is on higher side but worth visiting at-least once. Parking: Valet parking is available Kid-friendliness: Its kid friendly place

review_text: Update: After visiting here for 20+ times I am updating my review. Dont ever go here, after being a regular customer here and paying service charges always because I was frankly okay with it but today they surpassed all their limits. The manger behaved like he offered the food for free and was forcing service tax saying it is mandatory regardless of it being not mandated by the govt. He was trying to ego bash us in paying it but i didnt care and removed it, he said this is the only time he is removing it. So this is the last time I am visiting here and not recommending anyone to go here; Your dishes are already overpriced over that you want to force the service charge for pathetic service? Which is not mandatory (theyll just force it regardless) Hope they start respecting customers Previous review: Amazing Experience at Mahesh Lunch Home, their staff is awesome and welcoming plus the sea food is next level.

review_text: Indulging in sea food is a delightful experience, especially when treating a visiting friend. The attentive wait staff promptly guided us through a flavorful journey, recommending dishes tailored to our tastes. The mild-gravy crab proved a delicious choice, complemented by the delightful bombil Fry, Tandoori prawns, and a satisfying conclusion with caramel custard. The aam panna margarita emerged as a standout in the cocktail selection. For seafood enthusiasts, this restaurant is a must-visit, offering culinary adventure.

place_name: Mahesh Lunch Home - Seafood Specialty Restaurant (Juhu)
Mahesh Lunch Home - Seafood Specialty Restaurant (Juhu)
review_text: Everything about Maheshs was top draw!!,ranging from the ever so comforting set-up and ambience,the service-oriented mentality of the staff,the arrangements,cleanliness and above all the lip-smacking,mouth-watery delicacies,...the oh-so-many varieties of crab recipes..with reference from a wide range of regions, namely,Andhra,Konkan,to top it all,the best one being the Malay crab gravy which literally sets your taste buds soaring to the greatest of heights!!..It was a Crab n Wine festival we had gone to..the wines on order were also impressive..SULA being the best of it..Prawns,Fish,Chicken delicacies were aple nty but nothing to beat the Malay crab gravy which had a Thai green curry kind of flavour!!!.Not to forget,even the Veggie cuisine was awesome..The Dosa varieties,panneer masala gravy..couple of really delightful veggie wonders!!!Mahesh Lunch Home at Juhu is a must go-to place for any avid Mumbai City traveller and foodie!!!
